    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>Labor and parts quoted separately &mdash; and LA hard water is a factor you need to know about</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Most appliance repair companies in Los Angeles use flat-rate BlueBook pricing &mdash; a single bundled number before the technician has diagnosed anything. For dishwasher repairs, this is particularly misleading because a significant portion of LA dishwasher calls involve hard water mineral buildup rather than a failed component. A spray arm clogged with scale needs cleaning, not a replacement part. A flat rate before diagnosis means you might pay for parts you don&rsquo;t need.</p>
      <p>We diagnose first. The $89 fee covers the full diagnosis. Once we know what failed, we give you two numbers: labor and the specific OEM part needed (if any). You approve the quote before we start. Scale-related repairs often cost less than homeowners expect &mdash; cleaning is not a parts job.</p>
      <p>Los Angeles water runs 300&ndash;400 mg/L TDS. This is significantly harder than most US metro areas. Heating elements scale up faster, spray arms clog faster, and detergent dispensers can fail from mineral accumulation. We factor LA&rsquo;s water chemistry into every dishwasher diagnosis &mdash; and descaling is included in the repair when it&rsquo;s part of the root cause fix.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="water-block">
      <div class="water-label">&#128167; LA Hard Water &mdash; 300&ndash;400 mg/L TDS</div>
      <p>Los Angeles water is among the hardest in major US cities. Dishwasher mineral buildup happens significantly faster than manufacturer maintenance schedules assume. Spray arm jets clog, heating elements scale up reducing cleaning performance, and detergent dispensers stick from mineral accumulation. When we diagnose a dishwasher in LA, hard water is always part of the evaluation &mdash; not an afterthought.</p>
    </div>

