<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Cost Factors</p>
    <h2>What affects dishwasher repair cost in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="factors-grid">
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128167;</div><h3>LA hard water &mdash; 300&ndash;400 mg/L TDS</h3><p>The single biggest factor unique to LA. Scale buildup clogs spray arms, coats heating elements, and jams dispenser mechanisms. Hard water root causes are often free to fix &mdash; cleaning, not parts.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127991;</div><h3>Brand and part cost</h3><p>Bosch, Samsung, LG, and Whirlpool have widely available OEM parts. Miele uses European-sourced proprietary components at a significant premium &mdash; which is precisely why we quote parts separately.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128295;</div><h3>Type of failure</h3><p>A door latch swap is straightforward. A control board diagnosis takes more time to confirm. Separating labor and parts means the complexity of your specific repair is reflected in the price you see.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128197;</div><h3>Age of the unit</h3><p>Control boards and pump assemblies for 10+ year old dishwashers are sometimes discontinued or require lead time. We check parts availability before quoting repair.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127968;</div><h3>Built-in vs. portable</h3><p>Built-in dishwashers require pulling the unit from under the counter for certain repairs, adding labor time. We factor this into the quote before starting &mdash; transparent pricing mid-repair.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128204;</div><h3>Root cause vs. symptom</h3><p>A dishwasher not cleaning properly might be a clogged spray arm from hard water, not a failed pump. Replacing the pump without clearing the scale means the problem returns. We find the root cause.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Repair vs. Replace</p>
    <h2>When to repair a dishwasher, when to replace it</h2>
    <p class="lead">We give you an honest assessment after diagnosis. Dishwashers are generally cost-effective to repair &mdash; the math usually favors it.</p>
    <div class="rvr-grid">
      <div class="rvr-card repair">
        <h3>Repair makes sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Unit is under 10 years old</li>
          <li>Total repair (labor + parts) is under 50% of replacement value</li>
          <li>Failure is hard water related (often no parts cost)</li>
          <li>Single component failure &mdash; pump, latch, inlet valve</li>
          <li>Miele &mdash; these last 15+ years with proper repair</li>
          <li>Built-in unit in a custom kitchen &mdash; replacement requires cabinetry work</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rvr-card replace">
        <h3>Replace makes more sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Budget unit is 10&ndash;12+ years old</li>
          <li>Control board cost exceeds 60% of replacement value</li>
          <li>Multiple components failing simultaneously</li>
          <li>Tub cracked or structurally compromised</li>
          <li>Parts are discontinued with no reliable ETA</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

